##Why does Zhong Nanshan say it is confident that the outbreak is largely under control by the end of April?

The papernews

The function introduction, has the connotation the current politics new media

Wu Yi is a reporter for the paper

"from China's point of view, we are confident that we can basically control the epidemic by the end of April, " said Zhong Nanshan, a member of the Chinese Academy of Engineering and head of the National Health Commission's high-level Expert Group, at a news briefing for the Guangzhou Medical University on the epidemic prevention and control.

Why is Zhong Nanshan so confident of this conclusion? On February 28th, a research paper published in the Journal of Thoracic Disease (Jtd) entitled "Modified Seir and AI prediction of the epidemic trend of COVID-19 in China under public health interventions" (based on SEIR optimization model and AI to predict the outbreak trend of COVID-19 in China under public health intervention) provides the answer.

The corresponding author of the paper is Zhong Nanshan, a professor of respiratory medicine at Guangzhou Medical University and Director of the respiratory disease, the other corresponding author is he Jianxing, director of Thoracic Surgery at Guangzhou Medical University, head of the Guangzhou Institute of Respiratory Health and Head of the Study Group at the State key laboratory of respiratory diseases.

On January 23,2020, with the development of the epidemic of new coronavirus (COVID-19) , Wuhan announced the "closure of the city" . On that day, Hubei and even China took unprecedented measures to prevent and control the epidemic of new coronavirus, these measures include mass quarantine, strict movement controls and extensive surveillance of suspected cases.

Using epidemiological models and artificial intelligence, Zhong Nanshan's team predicted that the mainland epidemic would peak in late February and gradually decline by the end of April, the total number of patients infected by the final outbreak was about 120,000(95% confidence interval: 89,741 to 156794) .

If the implementation time of prevention and control measures (January 23) is delayed by five days, the data model predicts that the scale of the epidemic in the mainland will be nearly three times as large as that predicted. If the current quarantine prevention and control measures in Hubei are cancelled after the end of the Spring Festival holiday, it will trigger the second epidemic peak in the province in mid-march and extend the epidemic period to late April.

"strict surveillance and early detection and isolation policies should be maintained until the end of April 2020, " the team concluded, the epidemic prevention and control measures implemented in China since January 23 have been effective and necessary to reduce the scale of the epidemic.

Study: If Prevention and control intervention is delayed by 5 days, the scale of the epidemic on the mainland will nearly triple

According to the data model of Zhong Nanshan's research team, what exactly is the trend of the epidemic in China? First, the model was based on three data sources: First, the number of new cases of coronary pneumonia reported daily by the NHRC (confirmed cases were detected by real-time RT-PCR) . II. Daily migration data based on rail, air and road traffic movements. Data sets of SARS cases from April to June 2003 were used for AI data training.

Two data models are used in epidemic analysis: Seir Optimization Model (susceptibility-latency-infection-isolation epidemic model) and LSTM model (long-term short memory model) in deep learning.

Considering that the risk of transmission of NCP has decreased since the implementation of epidemic prevention and control measures in mainland China on January 23, according to the LSTM model, the NCP epidemic in mainland China will reach its peak on February 4, by the end of April there will be 95,000 cases.

The Seir model predicts that the mainland epidemic will peak on February 28, with 59,764 confirmed cases (95% confidence interval: 51,979 to 70,172)  The estimated final outbreak size was 122122 cases (95% confidence interval: 89,741 to 156794) .

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Prediction of epidemic situation in China by Seir and LSTM models.

What would happen if the timing of prevention and control interventions on the mainland (23 January) were delayed by five days, thereby increasing the chance of transmission of the virus? Based on this assumption, the Seir model predicts that the mainland epidemic will peak on March 4, with 173372 confirmed cases; by the end of April, the final epidemic will have reached 351874 cases, nearly triple the previous forecast. If the intervention had been implemented five days earlier, the final scale of the outbreak would have been 40,991.

"Our team made a predictive model of the epidemic, which peaked in mid-or late February, with about 60,000 or 70,000 confirmed cases, which were sent back to authoritative foreign journals. " On February 27, zhong Nanshan spoke about the team's research at a news briefing for the Guangzhou Medical University.

At the start of the outbreak, Zhong Nanshan said, an authoritative test model used by the epidemiologist predicted that the number of new cases in China would reach 160,000 in early February. "This is not taking into account the strong intervention of the state, nor the delay in resuming work after the Spring Festival. In fact, our prediction is closer to the authorities. "

The paper's www.thepaper.cn  , which collates data from the NHRC's website, found that the peak of the current total number of confirmed cases of NCP occurred on February 17, on that day, 31 provinces (autonomous regions and municipalities) and Xinjiang Production and Construction Corps reported 58,016 confirmed cases, bringing the total number of confirmed cases to 72,436.

This is very much in line with the Seir Model's prediction that the mainland epidemic peaked on February 28, with 59,764 confirmed cases and a 95% confidence interval between 51,979 and 70,172 cases, although the peak was 11 days earlier.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
February 6-march 2,31 provinces (autonomous regions, municipalities directly under the Central Government) and Xinjiang Production and Construction Corps patients with newly diagnosed and cumulative number of confirmed cases. Wu Yi, correspondent, thepaper.cn

From February 17 to March 2, the total number of confirmed cases of NCP decreased from 58,016 to 30,004. As of 2400 hours on March 2, a total of 80,151 confirmed cases have been reported in the mainland.

Two new peak periods for newly confirmed cases in mainland

In addition to the current number of confirmed cases, the number of newly confirmed cases per day is also an important indicator of the epidemic trend. The team found that between January 22 and February 10, the actual number of newly confirmed cases on the mainland closely matched the curve predicted by the LSTM. However, the Seir model predicts that there will be several small peaks of newly diagnosed cases in mid-to late February.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
The top figure is the cumulative number of confirmed cases predicted by the LSTM model, and the bottom figure is the number of newly confirmed cases predicted by Seir and LSTM models.

Both Seir and LSTM models predict that the mainland reached a single-day peak of new infections between February 4 and 7, with about 4,000 new confirmed cases per day.

The paper found two peaks in the number of newly diagnosed cases in a single day in the mainland from January 23 to March 2, one from February 3 to 7, according to data collated on the website of the National Health Commission, the newly diagnosed cases were 3235(February 3) , 3887(February 4) , 3694(February 5) , 3143(February 6) and 3399(February 7) , which were slightly lower than the predicted data of the above models.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
From January 23 to March 2, there were two peaks in the number of newly confirmed cases in a single day on the mainland. Wu Yi, correspondent, thepaper.cn

Another peak period occurred from February 12 to 13, when clinical cases were included in the statistics of confirmed cases in Hubei Province, leading to a sharp increase in the number of cases. On February 12, there were 15,152 newly confirmed cases (including 13,332 clinically diagnosed cases in Hubei Province) in the mainland, and on February 13 there were 5,090(including 3095 clinically diagnosed cases in Hubei Province) .

At present, the number of newly diagnosed cases per day in China is decreasing. A total of 125 new cases were confirmed on the mainland on March 2, according to the website of the National Health Commission. That was the lowest number confirmed in a single day since January 23.

PREDICTION: the Hubei outbreak will come to an end in late April

Since Wuhan was "closed" on January 23, cities and states in Hubei Province have also announced strict traffic control and quarantine measures.

Zhong Nanshan's team set the migration index for Hubei Province to zero after Feb. 10,2020, and based on the number of confirmed cases by Feb. 12, the model predicted that the epidemic would peak in Hubei Province on Feb. 20, the outbreak is expected to end in late April with a total of 59,578 cases (95% confidence interval between 39,189 and 66,591) confirmed.

However, the actual data of Hubei epidemic situation is higher than the forecast. As of 2400 hours on March 2, there were 67,217 confirmed cases in Hubei (49,426 in Wuhan) , according to the website of the National Health Commission.

In their paper, the team also noted that the number of confirmed cases and the epidemic curve based on PCR detection may underestimate the reality of the current diagnosis of NCP due to deficiencies in the process and methodology. The SARS epidemic data set (the number of cases from April to June 2003) was also used to predict the epidemic trend of NCP.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Prediction of epidemic situation in Hubei Province by Seir Model.

Should the current prevention and control measures in Hubei Province be relaxed, and what will be the consequences if they are relaxed?

The team hypothesized that after the end of the Spring Festival holiday, when the current quarantine restrictions are lifted and people are allowed to move about normally, the province will have its first epidemic peak on February 18 and its second on March 11, the final scale of the outbreak will increase by more than 13,000 cases compared with the scale of the ongoing control measures.

The research team stressed that in addition to the continued implementation of strict prevention, control and quarantine measures in Hubei, other provinces have invested large amounts of medical resources into Hubei to build new admission hospitals and quarantine centers, easing the shortage of local medical resources, this has reduced the risk of transmission of the virus, which has also contributed to the reduction in the scale of the epidemic.

As of February 10, there were 31,728,1,177 and 1,117 newly diagnosed cases of pneumonia in Hubei, Guangdong and Zhejiang provinces, accounting for 80% of the total number of cases in China.

In the end, Guangdong and Zhejiang did not trigger a new pneumonia pandemic. Seir model predicts that the epidemic in two provinces will reach its peak on February 20 and end in mid-april. The final epidemic scale in Guangdong is 1511 cases (95% confidence interval is 1097 cases to 1948 cases)  In Zhejiang, there were 1491 cases (95% confidence interval ranged from 1066 to 1851) .

As of 2400 hours on March 2,1350 and 1213 cases of newly diagnosed pneumonia had been reported in Guangdong and Zhejiang provinces, respectively, according to the websites of the provincial health and Health Commission. As the number of newly confirmed cases per day in Guangdong and Zhejiang gradually decreased to zero, the final scale of the epidemic may be more consistent with the above forecast data.

Guangdong and Zhejiang, the two provinces most affected by the outbreak after Hubei, have seen a slowdown in the growth of the epidemic as a result of strong implementation of control measures, the team said, indicating the effectiveness of quarantine and control measures. Continued "early detection and early isolation" measures could also be effective in preventing a second wave of epidemics in Guangdong and Zhejiang.

"In addition, temperature changes due to seasonal variations are important for the dissipation of the SARS epidemic in Guangdong Province. If the NCP epidemic develops according to this logic, the epidemic in Guangdong Province is expected to subside earlier than in Zhejiang and Hubei,"the team said.

However, it is important to note that with the international situation of new pneumonia gradually become severe, domestic also need to pay attention to imported cases of prevention and control. According to the provincial health commission's website, from 0-24 am on March 2, seven new cases of coronary pneumonia (all imported from Qingtian, Lishui) were confirmed in Zhejiang Province.

"At that time [ the study ] did not consider foreign countries, now the situation abroad has changed and there are other considerations, but from the Chinese point of view, we are confident that we can basically control the epidemic by the end of April, " Zhong Nanshan said in a news briefing for the Guangzhou Medical University event.
